column5: Weekend of the 21st of June. Looking forward to seeing you there.
I'll be there if the good Lord is willin' and the creek don't rise!... I wonder about the other 2/3rds of the Southern Contingincy?
LOL - Saw the post title - and I thought you were looking for one!!!   Don
I think that's our daughter's graduation....will have to confirm.  We'll likely miss the pike tourney, but hopefully we'll get to stay until Monday or Tuesday.
I'l be there for the entire week as always Kelvin, June 16 thru the 22nd.  Lookin forward to seeing you again.
Cabin 5.  June 15 to 22.  Running Sunday to Sunday - can't miss out on all the fun that Saturday.   Looking forward to another great week with great friends.
Art and I are in for sure.
I'll be there... not sure of the date's yet...  I can' wait for morning coffee with Lew again....  and of course... seeing everyone else...

Hoping to have a cabin from Sunday to Sunday....not sure if any are still available as I haven't been able to reach them....will have to call today I think....not sure what days I'll be there as I couldn't get the weeks vacation for it...still working on that though, but Beans will be there and quite possibly my mom as well...at least on the days I'm not   someone needs to look after the zoo  Maureen
Always good yakkin with you before sun-up Shelley, a great way to start the day
This year I will not be in the area for the G2G as I will be on the south shore of L. Nipissing, Cant wait for the reports though!!  G
South Shore to West Arm should only be an hours drive...No?
An hour and a half in a boat @25-30 MPH Beans. In good weather. Took 2.5 to get there last year in rough water. By vehicle would take about 2 hrs. Its a long way around from the south end.

Not sure what our plans are this coming summer. We may come SOUTH for Lakair again.. but not sure about a whole week this time.  I know, I know.. I'm supposed to stay up at the lake and just send Leah !

Well fishergirl72 and myself would sure like to make the trip this year,its just so close to my july1st holidays and we always head north to the ottawa river and do a few weeks of walleye fishing,and its a money thing too!!!so maybe we can figure out a plan and do both,it would be great to see everyone and have fun,and of course catch a few walleyes for a nice big shore lunch !!!....cheers

Well I've officially booked my cabin today   We'll have the cabin from the 15th to the 22nd this year, as well as a docking space for the boat ..lots more    for at least one of us   I didn't get that week off for my vacation this year    but I'm working on it.  At the very least Beans will be up there as well as my mom for the days I'm not.  Maureen
